Return the number of elements in the source
array
.IR s .
Sort
the contents of
.I s
using
.IR gawk\^ "'s"
normal rules for
comparing values, and replace the indices of the
sorted values
.I s
with sequential
integers starting with 1. If the optional
destination array
.I d
is specified,
first duplicate
.I s
into
.IR d ,
and then sort
.IR d ,
leaving the indices of the
source array
